Package gov.nih.nlm.bioscores.candidate

Class CandidateSalience

  • java.lang.Object
    • gov.nih.nlm.bioscores.candidate.CandidateSalience

  • public class CandidateSalience
extends java.lang.Object
    This class defines methods to break ties between a number of candidate referents that are equally likely to corefer with the coreferential mention. A pre-defined salience method is used as a PostScoringCandidateFilter to find the best referent.

    Currently, five salience methods are defined. These are:

    • CandidateSalience.Type.Proximity: The referent closest to the mention is selected.
    • CandidateSalience.Type.ParseTree: The referent closest to the mention on the parse tree is selected.
    • CandidateSalience.Type.FirstTerm: The first compatible referent that appears in the document is selected.
    • CandidateSalience.Type.FocusTerm: The term that is the document focus is selected.
    • CandidateSalience.Type.FreqCount: The compatible term that occurs most in the document is selected.
    The implementation of CandidateSalience.Type.FocusTerm is incomplete; currently, the focus term is taken to be the same as the first term. CandidateSalience.Type.Proximity and CandidateSalience.Type.ParseTree have been useful; the usefulness of the other methods may be very limited.
    Author:
    Halil Kilicoglu
